1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,002
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,086 --> 00:00:08,466
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:10,552
- <i>♪ Fix it</i> ♪
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,635 --> 00:00:12,804
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,887 --> 00:00:16,224
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:17,225 --> 00:00:19,811
[Atoy] <i>Tatoy has something to tell you.</i>

7
00:00:20,395 --> 00:00:21,855
Are you okay?

8
00:00:21,938 --> 00:00:22,856
Mm-hmm.

9
00:00:22,939 --> 00:00:25,108
You look like you're crying.

10
00:00:25,191 --> 00:00:28,862
[Mabel] <i>But even if you're his child now,</i>
<i>he's still Ibyang's daddy, right?</i>

11
00:00:28,945 --> 00:00:31,448
Because I saw them together
in the classroom.

12
00:00:31,531 --> 00:00:33,158
Why didn't he come to me?

13
00:00:33,241 --> 00:00:36,578
[friend 2] <i>Maybe he only wants</i>
<i>Ibyang to be his daughter.</i>

14
00:00:36,661 --> 00:00:37,620
[Janine] <i>I'm the real daughter.</i>

15
00:00:37,704 --> 00:00:39,456
<i>He's just your pretend daddy.</i>

16
00:00:40,123 --> 00:00:40,999
Right, Daddy?

17
00:00:41,082 --> 00:00:44,252
[Ibyang] <i>Is what Janine said true?</i>

18
00:00:44,335 --> 00:00:47,005
I just didn't know how to tell you.

19
00:00:47,088 --> 00:00:49,340
[Ibyang] <i>But why weren't you</i>
<i>honest with me?</i>

20
00:00:50,467 --> 00:00:51,968
[Atoy] <i>I love you both.</i>

21
00:00:52,051 --> 00:00:53,219
PREVIOUSLY

22
00:00:53,303 --> 00:00:55,013
[Janine] <i>Why are you hugging her?</i>

23
00:00:55,096 --> 00:00:56,598
He's not your father!

24
00:00:57,182 --> 00:01:01,311
Even if she didn't really come from me,
I still treat her like my own child.

25
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:03,688
[Atoy] <i>You're both important to me.</i>

26
00:01:04,314 --> 00:01:07,734
[Tonet] <i>But, brother,</i>
<i>you should have prepared Ibyang.</i>

27
00:01:07,817 --> 00:01:09,444
I feel bad for her.

28
00:01:09,527 --> 00:01:11,446
She deserves to know everything, right?

29
00:01:11,529 --> 00:01:12,572
Daddy!

30
00:01:13,531 --> 00:01:15,241
Can you take me home?

31
00:01:15,325 --> 00:01:17,869
[Janine] <i>Um, then let's go</i>
<i>to the house first.</i>

32
00:01:17,952 --> 00:01:19,204
I'm so happy.

33
00:01:19,287 --> 00:01:22,916
Maybe there's still a chance
he'll get back together with Audrey.

34
00:01:22,999 --> 00:01:24,125
[Tonet] <i>That's why he's like this.</i>

35
00:01:24,209 --> 00:01:25,126
No, not at all.

36
00:01:25,210 --> 00:01:27,462
[Atoy] <i>This is really just for the child.</i>

37
00:01:27,545 --> 00:01:29,214
It's over. I have no interest in her.

38
00:01:29,297 --> 00:01:31,090
I want to go to my daddy.

39
00:01:31,174 --> 00:01:32,258
[in English] What?

40
00:01:32,342 --> 00:01:34,761
If you don't let me,
I don't want you anymore!

41
00:01:34,844 --> 00:01:36,888
[Gavin] In the short time
I've known Brother Atoy,

42
00:01:36,971 --> 00:01:39,349
I feel like he can discipline Janine.

43
00:01:39,891 --> 00:01:41,893
He's a good father to Ibyang.

44
00:01:41,976 --> 00:01:44,354
[music fades]

45
00:01:44,979 --> 00:01:46,231
- [phone rings]
- [Atoy] You guys are too much.

46
00:01:47,232 --> 00:01:48,775
[Atoy] You're making up stories.

47
00:01:48,858 --> 00:01:50,360
- Brother!
- [Atoy] Oh?

48
00:01:50,443 --> 00:01:51,945
Audrey is calling.

49
00:01:52,445 --> 00:01:53,279
I'll reject it.

50
00:01:53,363 --> 00:01:55,240
Since you said you have
no interest, right?

51
00:01:55,323 --> 00:01:56,866
- Hey, hey.
- Gi… Give it to me!

52
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,785
Why are you panicking if it's nothing?

53
00:01:58,868 --> 00:02:01,037
- [phone ringing]
- [whimsical music playing]

54
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:02,539
Oh? Yes.

55
00:02:03,706 --> 00:02:05,625
It's nothing. Shut up.

56
00:02:07,502 --> 00:02:09,379
Uh, hello, Audrey?

57
00:02:09,462 --> 00:02:10,380
[music stops]

58
00:02:11,005 --> 00:02:13,383
Uh, sorry. I didn't answer
right away because…

59
00:02:13,466 --> 00:02:14,926
[sharp inhale] Yes.

60
00:02:16,219 --> 00:02:19,514
[music resumes]

61
00:02:20,098 --> 00:02:22,642
- Or… Or maybe he's talking to Janine.
- Uh…

62
00:02:22,725 --> 00:02:25,770
Because didn't he say he felt thrilled
when she called him daddy? Yes.

63
00:02:25,854 --> 00:02:28,731
But it looks like Audrey
is the one calling.

64
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:31,484
- [Ame] Huh?
- My godson's smile is different.

65
00:02:31,568 --> 00:02:32,861
There's a spark.

66
00:02:34,362 --> 00:02:36,990
- Mm. He said it's nothing.
- Oh, no.

67
00:02:37,073 --> 00:02:38,908
He said it's for the child.

68
00:02:41,452 --> 00:02:42,287
[in English] Ouch.

69
00:02:42,370 --> 00:02:45,123
[in English] It hurts so much!

70
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:47,458
[laughs] You're not even together!

71
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:48,835
[Karla] Why ouch?

72
00:02:50,211 --> 00:02:53,089
- [Karla chuckles]
- [Ame moans]

73
00:02:54,090 --> 00:02:56,259
[suave theme music playing]

74
00:03:19,574 --> 00:03:20,909
[music fades]

75
00:03:20,992 --> 00:03:24,203
This banana cue is so bland,
even with all the sugar.

76
00:03:25,246 --> 00:03:28,124
I can't taste the sweetness too.

77
00:03:28,207 --> 00:03:30,752
This is what happens
when you're unlucky in love.

78
00:03:30,835 --> 00:03:33,338
When the person you like
doesn't like you back.

79
00:03:33,421 --> 00:03:34,797
[Karla scoffs]

80
00:03:34,881 --> 00:03:36,049
[in English] Same, girl.

81
00:03:36,132 --> 00:03:37,050
You too?

82
00:03:37,550 --> 00:03:40,345
Hmm. You know about Gavin, right?

83
00:03:40,845 --> 00:03:43,306
Speaking of, let's meet
later at the court.

84
00:03:44,015 --> 00:03:45,266
Help me out.

85
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:49,896
Why did you even agree to set
a date for Gavin and Cathy?

86
00:03:49,979 --> 00:03:51,981
You're worse than us.

87
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:53,566
[Tonet] Are you a masochist, girl?

88
00:03:53,650 --> 00:03:56,653
Say whatever you want to say about me.

89
00:03:56,736 --> 00:03:58,404
Just help me.

90
00:03:58,488 --> 00:04:01,532
Of course. No one gets left behind
among the heartbroken.

91
00:04:01,616 --> 00:04:02,450
[Karla] Hm-mm.

92
00:04:03,034 --> 00:04:04,577
[Ame] Oh, girl.

93
00:04:04,661 --> 00:04:06,204
[Karla] Oh, there's a car.

94
00:04:06,287 --> 00:04:11,709
[pensive music playing]

95
00:04:12,669 --> 00:04:14,045
[Audrey] Dear, come on.

96
00:04:14,128 --> 00:04:15,338
[Ame] Can you get me some drinks?

97
00:04:15,421 --> 00:04:16,506
- [Audrey, in English] Excuse me.
- [Atoy] Oh.

98
00:04:16,589 --> 00:04:17,799
[Audrey] Oh, Atoy.

99
00:04:19,717 --> 00:04:21,052
- [in English] Say hi to Dad, my dear.
- [Janine] Oh!

100
00:04:21,135 --> 00:04:22,595
- Daddy!
- [Tonet] She's smiling, look.

101
00:04:22,679 --> 00:04:23,638
[Atoy grunts]

102
00:04:24,889 --> 00:04:25,974
[Audrey chuckles softly]

103
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:28,434
Thank you.

104
00:04:28,518 --> 00:04:29,978
You allowed our child to come here.

105
00:04:30,561 --> 00:04:34,857
She insisted, so I said
just for this weekend.

106
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:37,235
So you behave, dear, okay?

107
00:04:37,318 --> 00:04:39,821
Call me if you need anything.

108
00:04:39,904 --> 00:04:42,407
I hope I won't regret this decision.

109
00:04:44,826 --> 00:04:45,660
I'll take care of it.

110
00:04:45,743 --> 00:04:47,537
- Uh, Tonet…
- [Atoy] Ah…

111
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:51,874
Thank you. You've been
very understanding of our situation.

112
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:55,712
Um, Atoy is lucky
to have you as a girlfriend.

113
00:04:55,795 --> 00:04:59,841
- Ah, girlfriend? They're not together! No.
- [Tonet] Ame, c'mon!

114
00:04:59,924 --> 00:05:01,551
- You're unbelievable.
- [Audrey] Is that so?

115
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:04,387
[Tonet] You really had to say that.

116
00:05:04,470 --> 00:05:07,557
Give me back the money
I used to buy you banana cue!

117
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:10,018
- Wow, sis.
- Why? It's true what I said!

118
00:05:10,101 --> 00:05:12,603
Ms. Audrey, they're not together.

119
00:05:12,687 --> 00:05:14,314
Tonet is just hoping.

120
00:05:14,397 --> 00:05:16,024
- Ah--
- Mmm-mmm.

121
00:05:16,107 --> 00:05:18,735
Better to be hopeful
than to be delusional.

122
00:05:18,818 --> 00:05:20,528
By the way, this is Ame.

123
00:05:20,611 --> 00:05:24,157
Ame and Karla, Miss Cita's daughter.

124
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:25,658
Psst! Get out of here!

125
00:05:26,534 --> 00:05:28,244
[Audrey] Okay, you take care.

126
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:32,123
[in English] Bye, dear. Love you.

127
00:05:32,206 --> 00:05:33,333
Thank you.

128
00:05:33,875 --> 00:05:36,461
Don't worry. Um… I'll take care of her.

129
00:05:36,544 --> 00:05:39,172
[bright music playing]

130
00:05:45,428 --> 00:05:46,846
[Janine] Bye.

131
00:05:46,929 --> 00:05:47,930
Come on.

132
00:05:51,059 --> 00:05:52,185
[Atoy] Come in.

133
00:05:54,437 --> 00:05:55,563
[Cita] Hi, Janine!

134
00:05:55,646 --> 00:05:57,356
I'm Miss Cita!

135
00:05:58,316 --> 00:05:59,984
Are you the maid here?

136
00:06:00,818 --> 00:06:01,861
[Atoy] Uh, no, Janine.

137
00:06:02,653 --> 00:06:04,197
No, she's my godmother.

138
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:06,574
She works here in the shop.

139
00:06:06,657 --> 00:06:08,451
Actually, she's been working here
for a long time.

140
00:06:08,534 --> 00:06:12,288
She helps us here, assists,
and she also knows how to sew.

141
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:15,541
[in English] Ah, okay.

142
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:16,959
[Atoy] This is where I work.

143
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:20,963
I inherited this from my father,
your Grandpa Delfin.

144
00:06:21,047 --> 00:06:23,007
He was the original tailor.

145
00:06:23,091 --> 00:06:27,053
The best tailor here
in Barangay Tabang Lupa.

146
00:06:27,136 --> 00:06:29,388
That's why it's called
Mang Delfin's Tailoring.

147
00:06:30,389 --> 00:06:31,307
[in English] Okay.

148
00:06:32,141 --> 00:06:33,434
Where's Ibyang?

149
00:06:33,518 --> 00:06:36,312
Ah, in her room, doing her assignment.

150
00:06:36,938 --> 00:06:38,231
That's good.

151
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:42,443
Uh, Janine, sorry.

152
00:06:42,527 --> 00:06:44,570
My house is just like this.

153
00:06:44,654 --> 00:06:47,073
It's a bit small, but don't worry.

154
00:06:47,698 --> 00:06:48,825
It's decent.

155
00:06:49,742 --> 00:06:52,829
It's okay. As long as I'm with my daddy.

156
00:06:53,746 --> 00:06:55,623
[bright music playing]

157
00:06:56,290 --> 00:06:59,377
Uh, what do you want… Are you hungry?

158
00:06:59,460 --> 00:07:00,920
Do you want me to cook for you?

159
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:04,048
What do we have in the fridge?

160
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:05,424
What's your favorite?

161
00:07:05,925 --> 00:07:07,385
Oh, I know. Do you want us to go out?

162
00:07:07,468 --> 00:07:09,512
I can take you around here--

163
00:07:09,595 --> 00:07:11,389
Ah, no. I'll get you a snack first.

164
00:07:11,472 --> 00:07:13,433
Ah, I know we still have
chocolate rice porridge left.

165
00:07:13,516 --> 00:07:14,767
Okay. Wait!

166
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:17,019
[pensive music playing]

167
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:17,937
‪[dramatic sting]

168
00:07:22,733 --> 00:07:24,527
Atoy keeps denying it.

169
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:27,780
But it's obvious he still
has feelings for Audrey.

170
00:07:29,866 --> 00:07:31,492
You're jealous.

171
00:07:32,076 --> 00:07:32,910
[Emerson] Hmm?

172
00:07:32,994 --> 00:07:35,288
You don't have to hide it.

173
00:07:35,371 --> 00:07:37,957
I know you like Atoy.

174
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:43,129
But for me, just don't
let him hurt you, okay?

175
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:45,756
Hmm!

176
00:07:46,507 --> 00:07:49,594
[light music playing]

177
00:07:49,677 --> 00:07:52,513
My brother is so sweet!

178
00:07:53,055 --> 00:07:54,390
[scoffs, mutters]

179
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:56,267
That's why you're my brother.

180
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:57,685
Ouch. Ouch, ouch!

181
00:07:57,768 --> 00:07:59,270
Of course!

182
00:07:59,353 --> 00:08:04,484
It's a brother's job to protect
his younger siblings.

183
00:08:05,318 --> 00:08:07,111
Aww. Thank you, brother.

184
00:08:07,195 --> 00:08:08,404
That's why you're my brother!

185
00:08:08,488 --> 00:08:09,989
- I love you so much!
- [chuckles]

186
00:08:10,072 --> 00:08:11,657
- [chuckles]
- Okay. Fine, fine, fine.

187
00:08:11,741 --> 00:08:13,576
I know, I know. I love you too.

188
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:20,416
But if Atoy really doesn't like me,
that's fine!

189
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:23,544
Then I'll just find another guy.

190
00:08:24,378 --> 00:08:26,380
There's only one person who matters to me,

191
00:08:26,464 --> 00:08:29,300
and I don't want to lose him.

192
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,594
Who?

193
00:08:32,261 --> 00:08:33,429
You!

194
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:34,805
- You, silly.
- [laughs]

195
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:36,724
Who else would it be! It can't be him.

196
00:08:36,807 --> 00:08:38,267
[laughs]

197
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:39,185
Okay, okay.

198
00:08:39,268 --> 00:08:42,438
All right, all right, all right.
You're so dramatic! So dramatic.

199
00:08:42,522 --> 00:08:44,148
It's fine. There's global warming.

200
00:08:44,232 --> 00:08:45,441
This is the first time
we've hugged like this.

201
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:46,651
Fine, fine, fine.

202
00:08:46,734 --> 00:08:48,236
[in English] I love you too.
I love you too.

203
00:08:48,319 --> 00:08:50,488
Wait. Finish it already.
Ouch. Finish it already.

204
00:08:50,571 --> 00:08:51,989
Finish what you're doing.

205
00:08:52,073 --> 00:08:52,907
Okay.

206
00:08:52,990 --> 00:08:53,950
Go ahead.

207
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:55,743
[chuckles]

208
00:09:05,002 --> 00:09:07,046
[music fades]

209
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:09,549
Brother Kurt, is everything cooked?

210
00:09:09,632 --> 00:09:12,009
[in English] Yes, ma'am! Ready to serve!

211
00:09:12,593 --> 00:09:13,928
- Are you sure it's delicious?
- Oh.

212
00:09:14,011 --> 00:09:15,346
What if Cathy doesn't like it?

213
00:09:15,429 --> 00:09:18,015
Hmm, of course! My spaghetti is al dente.

214
00:09:19,934 --> 00:09:23,688
Sis Ame, the tablecloth
doesn't look right.

215
00:09:23,771 --> 00:09:24,605
Hmm?

216
00:09:24,689 --> 00:09:25,731
[Karla] It's uneven on the left.

217
00:09:27,525 --> 00:09:28,776
[Karla] Let's fix it.

218
00:09:32,446 --> 00:09:34,991
Ah, excuse me! Ha! What if you help me?

219
00:09:35,074 --> 00:09:36,951
This is so heavy.

220
00:09:39,036 --> 00:09:42,540
- [Karla mutters]
- This is too much preparation, Karla.

221
00:09:42,623 --> 00:09:43,874
It would make sense
if you were the one on the date!

222
00:09:44,458 --> 00:09:47,461
Exactly. Why did you even agree to this?

223
00:09:48,045 --> 00:09:49,046
[Karla] Hmm…

224
00:09:50,506 --> 00:09:52,216
[gentle music playing]

225
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:53,301
Hey, boss.

226
00:09:55,428 --> 00:09:56,554
[Gavin] Wow!

227
00:09:58,014 --> 00:09:59,348
It's beautiful!

228
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,184
You're amazing, Karla!

229
00:10:02,810 --> 00:10:03,811
[in English] I owe you one.

230
00:10:03,894 --> 00:10:05,229
Hmm.

231
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:07,148
There you go.

232
00:10:28,169 --> 00:10:29,670
You owe me, okay?

233
00:10:30,963 --> 00:10:32,715
You said no backing out.

234
00:10:32,798 --> 00:10:35,259
Of course. Wait. I'll just pick her up.

235
00:10:45,936 --> 00:10:47,813
Is your heart ready to get hurt?

236
00:10:47,897 --> 00:10:49,690
Sis Ame, don't be pesky.

237
00:10:49,774 --> 00:10:50,900
[scoffs]

238
00:10:50,983 --> 00:10:55,988
But Karla, we'll be here to pick up
the pieces of your broken heart.

239
00:10:56,072 --> 00:10:56,906
[gasps]

240
00:10:56,989 --> 00:10:58,324
[Ame] Yes.

241
00:10:59,867 --> 00:11:00,826
[sighs]

242
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:02,745
Hmm, you can do it. We're here now.

243
00:11:02,828 --> 00:11:04,121
- [Ame mutters]
- [Tonet] Okay, go.

244
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:06,624
[music fades]

245
00:11:06,707 --> 00:11:08,167
- [in English] Oh, there you are.
- Cathy.

246
00:11:08,250 --> 00:11:09,669
- [chuckles softly]
- [in English] Flowers for you.

247
00:11:10,544 --> 00:11:11,712
- [in English] For me?
- Yes.

248
00:11:11,796 --> 00:11:13,089
You're so sweet.

249
00:11:13,172 --> 00:11:15,216
Why? What's the occasion?

250
00:11:15,299 --> 00:11:16,550
Just come with me.

251
00:11:16,634 --> 00:11:17,468
- Huh?
- Let's go.

252
00:11:17,551 --> 00:11:18,677
Where?

253
00:11:19,178 --> 00:11:21,263
- Just come with me.
- Why-- What's going on?

254
00:11:22,014 --> 00:11:24,392
[romantic music playing]

255
00:11:24,475 --> 00:11:27,603
[Ame] Put this… This flower,
let's put it in the middle of the table.

256
00:11:27,686 --> 00:11:29,563
- [Tonet] Why?
- [Cathy] What's going on?

257
00:11:33,442 --> 00:11:34,443
[gasps]

258
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,696
Wow. [titters]

259
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:39,532
[in English] You did this?

260
00:11:39,615 --> 00:11:41,659
[in English] Yes, anything for you.

261
00:11:41,742 --> 00:11:42,827
[in English] Do you like it?

262
00:11:44,703 --> 00:11:46,622
[chuckles] Just you?

263
00:11:47,456 --> 00:11:49,834
Actually, Karla helped me.

264
00:11:53,254 --> 00:11:54,213
They're with me.

265
00:11:54,296 --> 00:11:56,465
[giggles]

266
00:11:56,549 --> 00:11:57,675
We're here to assist you.

267
00:11:57,758 --> 00:12:01,053
If you want anything for your date.

268
00:12:01,137 --> 00:12:02,263
[Tonet] Mmm-mmm.

269
00:12:02,346 --> 00:12:04,014
[in English] Happy to serve! [titters]

270
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:06,434
[in English] Yes. Yes, happy to serve.

271
00:12:09,854 --> 00:12:13,774
So… was this your idea?

272
00:12:15,985 --> 00:12:17,528
[in English] It's… It's nice!

273
00:12:18,654 --> 00:12:22,450
A bit cheesy,
but it's, um, it's… it's nice.

274
00:12:27,538 --> 00:12:28,998
[in English] Uh, wait.

275
00:12:29,081 --> 00:12:30,624
You know basketball, right?

276
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:33,919
- Yes.
- [Cathy] Teach me first.

277
00:12:34,003 --> 00:12:36,088
- [Gavin] Okay, let's go.
- [in English] Let's play.

278
00:12:36,881 --> 00:12:38,632
- [Ame] Oh…
- [Cathy] I'll put my bag back.

279
00:12:38,716 --> 00:12:39,592
[Tonet stammers]

280
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:44,847
You know, she's so fussy.

281
00:12:46,807 --> 00:12:49,393
She didn't even say thank you.
She just criticized.

282
00:12:49,477 --> 00:12:50,853
Wh-What did Gavin see in her?

283
00:12:51,645 --> 00:12:53,439
[Tonet] He must be blind.

284
00:12:53,522 --> 00:12:54,648
[Ame] So--

285
00:12:54,732 --> 00:12:55,566
[music fades]

286
00:12:55,649 --> 00:12:56,859
[knocks on door]

287
00:12:58,194 --> 00:12:59,612
Hi, Ibyang!

288
00:13:00,863 --> 00:13:02,281
[pensive music playing]

289
00:13:02,364 --> 00:13:05,159
Uh… What are you doing here?

290
00:13:06,035 --> 00:13:09,622
Ibyang, Janine is here for the weekend.

291
00:13:10,247 --> 00:13:13,125
So, she'll stay in your room.
You'll share the room.

292
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:18,464
Daddy, it looks like
Ibyang doesn't want me here.

293
00:13:18,547 --> 00:13:21,133
It looks like she doesn't want me around.

294
00:13:22,092 --> 00:13:23,928
[tense unsettling music playing]

295
00:13:29,141 --> 00:13:30,851
Ha-- I'm happy.

296
00:13:34,813 --> 00:13:37,566
Your room is so small, Ibyang.

297
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:40,736
It's about the size of our bathroom.

298
00:13:40,819 --> 00:13:43,280
[sneaky music playing]

299
00:13:43,364 --> 00:13:44,490
No aircon?

300
00:13:45,783 --> 00:13:48,118
My room has aircon.

301
00:13:49,745 --> 00:13:51,914
Then stay there instead.

302
00:13:52,623 --> 00:13:53,666
Hey, Ibyang,

303
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:56,418
I'm just telling the truth.

304
00:13:56,502 --> 00:13:57,795
Why? Are you mad?

305
00:13:57,878 --> 00:14:01,006
No, I'm just saying too.

306
00:14:02,424 --> 00:14:03,884
[Atoy] Psst, that's enough.

307
00:14:06,011 --> 00:14:09,014
My child, you know,
at night, it's cold here.

308
00:14:09,682 --> 00:14:11,559
You don't need aircon.

309
00:14:11,642 --> 00:14:12,601
The electric fan is fine.

310
00:14:13,686 --> 00:14:15,980
Huh? Oh, okay?

311
00:14:17,022 --> 00:14:18,440
I don't want you fighting.

312
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:20,818
Yes, Tatoy.

313
00:14:21,402 --> 00:14:24,655
Will I sleep in Ibyang's bed?

314
00:14:25,739 --> 00:14:27,741
Yes. You'll sleep side by side.

315
00:14:27,825 --> 00:14:31,328
You'll sleep together here,
and I don't want fighting,

316
00:14:31,412 --> 00:14:33,873
because I want you to get along.

317
00:14:33,956 --> 00:14:35,124
Do you understand?

318
00:14:35,207 --> 00:14:37,167
You'll sleep side by side.

319
00:14:37,251 --> 00:14:38,502
Ame will stay in my room.

320
00:14:38,586 --> 00:14:39,753
I'll sleep downstairs.

321
00:14:40,671 --> 00:14:42,756
- Okay?
- Yes, Tatoy.

322
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:45,217
[Janine] I'll just sleep
beside you, Daddy.

323
00:14:45,301 --> 00:14:46,844
[in English] Please?

324
00:14:46,927 --> 00:14:47,970
Stay here.

325
00:14:48,053 --> 00:14:51,765
I want you beside Ibyang,
so you'll get along.

326
00:14:51,849 --> 00:14:53,517
I want you to bond.

327
00:14:54,101 --> 00:14:55,436
Okay? And no fighting.

328
00:14:55,519 --> 00:14:57,187
Do you understand me? Hmm?

329
00:14:57,271 --> 00:14:58,564
- Janine, Ibyang?
- [Janine sighs]

330
00:14:58,647 --> 00:15:01,025
- Yes, Tatoy.
- [in English] Yes, Daddy.

331
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:01,984
All right.

332
00:15:03,068 --> 00:15:03,903
‪[thud]

333
00:15:08,365 --> 00:15:11,493
[sneaky music playing]

334
00:15:17,249 --> 00:15:18,918
- [Cathy] I already know how!
- [Gavin] Oh!

335
00:15:19,001 --> 00:15:19,919
Why do I look like a pro?

336
00:15:20,002 --> 00:15:21,462
[Gavin] You're good.

337
00:15:21,545 --> 00:15:23,631
- [bustling chatter]
- [squeals softly]

338
00:15:23,714 --> 00:15:25,674
[Cathy, in English]
Oh, my gosh. That was so close.

339
00:15:25,758 --> 00:15:27,009
- [Cathy] Just a little.
- One more, one more.

340
00:15:27,092 --> 00:15:28,135
[Cathy] Okay, my turn.

341
00:15:30,387 --> 00:15:31,722
[Cathy, in English] Oh my God.

342
00:15:34,141 --> 00:15:35,434
[somber music playing]

343
00:15:35,517 --> 00:15:37,311
- [Tonet mutters]
- Cathy. Hey, Cathy.

344
00:15:37,394 --> 00:15:38,646
- No.
- Okay, I'll do it.

345
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:40,272
It's fine, I'll do it.

346
00:15:44,026 --> 00:15:48,155
[romantic music playing]

347
00:16:09,051 --> 00:16:10,386
[in English] Gavin, catch!

348
00:16:12,221 --> 00:16:13,055
- [clatters]
- [squeals and gasps]

349
00:16:13,138 --> 00:16:14,556
[Tonet] Oh my gosh!

350
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:15,641
[Karla, in English] Oh my gosh!

351
00:16:16,725 --> 00:16:17,559
[Karla] She got burned.

352
00:16:17,643 --> 00:16:18,727
- [in English] I'm so sorry.
- [Karla, in English] Water!

353
00:16:18,811 --> 00:16:20,062
- [in English] Oh my God.
- [Karla] Hey, water!

354
00:16:20,145 --> 00:16:22,356
- I'm so sorry, I'm so sorry!
- [Ame, panicking] Water! Water!

355
00:16:22,439 --> 00:16:24,274
- [Karla] Water! Brother Kurt, fire!
- [Ame] Oh!

356
00:16:24,358 --> 00:16:25,401
- [Cathy, in English] Oh my gosh!
- [Tonet] Water!

357
00:16:25,484 --> 00:16:27,903
[clamoring, shrieks]

358
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:29,321
I'll go ahead.

359
00:16:29,405 --> 00:16:31,615
There's a blood drive early tomorrow.

360
00:16:31,699 --> 00:16:33,033
Are you donating?

361
00:16:33,117 --> 00:16:35,536
Miss Siony already went around earlier.

362
00:16:35,619 --> 00:16:36,704
I signed up too.

363
00:16:36,787 --> 00:16:39,581
[Cita sighs, groans]

364
00:16:40,874 --> 00:16:41,834
Oh?

365
00:16:42,668 --> 00:16:44,503
You're sleeping here?

366
00:16:44,586 --> 00:16:46,714
There's no space upstairs.

367
00:16:46,797 --> 00:16:47,631
[Cita chuckles]

368
00:16:47,715 --> 00:16:50,384
You'll really do everything
for your child, huh?

369
00:16:50,467 --> 00:16:51,969
How are the kids?

370
00:16:52,594 --> 00:16:57,349
Well, they seem to be getting along.

371
00:16:58,559 --> 00:17:00,352
Hmm, that's good if so.

372
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:02,896
[Atoy] That's really my dream.

373
00:17:03,939 --> 00:17:07,359
I hope they'll treat
each other like sisters.

374
00:17:07,443 --> 00:17:09,570
Like real sisters.

375
00:17:09,653 --> 00:17:12,239
[chuckles] It's a nice wish.

376
00:17:12,322 --> 00:17:16,243
But it will only happen
if you really want it.

377
00:17:16,326 --> 00:17:19,204
You know Janine's attitude. Hmm?

378
00:17:20,706 --> 00:17:22,624
You should rest already. Okay.

379
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:24,126
- [indistinct]
- Lock up here.

380
00:17:24,209 --> 00:17:25,419
- [in English] Good night.
- [Cita] Okay.

381
00:17:25,502 --> 00:17:29,673
[pensive music playing]

382
00:17:29,757 --> 00:17:31,800
Here's your pillow.

383
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:33,927
Just one?

384
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:38,474
[music fades]

385
00:17:38,557 --> 00:17:39,725
I'll take this too.

386
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:43,437
But that's my pillow.

387
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:47,524
And Tatoy said we should share!

388
00:17:47,608 --> 00:17:48,442
[Janine scoffs]

389
00:17:48,525 --> 00:17:50,652
I don't want to share with you.

390
00:17:50,736 --> 00:17:55,115
I thought you came here
because we're okay now.

391
00:17:55,199 --> 00:17:59,536
And Tatoy said we shouldn't fight, right?

392
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:02,122
Ibyang, I only said that.

393
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:07,419
Actually, I'm here because
I'm afraid you'll take Daddy from me.

394
00:18:08,587 --> 00:18:10,714
You shouldn't even be here.

395
00:18:10,798 --> 00:18:12,132
[inhales]

396
00:18:12,216 --> 00:18:13,634
[pensive music playing]

397
00:18:13,717 --> 00:18:14,635
Why don't you leave?

398
00:18:15,719 --> 00:18:17,012
You go home.

399
00:18:17,846 --> 00:18:19,014
Me?

400
00:18:19,098 --> 00:18:20,766
I should leave?

401
00:18:21,725 --> 00:18:24,228
You should leave. Leave now! Leave!

402
00:18:24,311 --> 00:18:25,521
[Ibyang] Why?

403
00:18:26,146 --> 00:18:28,148
- [Janine] Leave, leave!
- [Ibyang gasps]

404
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:29,983
- Leave!
- [Ibyang mutters]

405
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:35,280
[tense music playing]

406
00:18:35,364 --> 00:18:37,032
[Ibyang] Hey, open this!

407
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:38,325
[Janine] Stay there.

408
00:18:38,909 --> 00:18:39,868
[knocking on door]

409
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:41,620
‪[knocking on door]

410
00:18:43,038 --> 00:18:44,289
[Ibyang] Hey, Janine.

411
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:46,792
Open this door!

412
00:18:47,292 --> 00:18:48,502
[Tonet] Oh my God!

413
00:18:48,585 --> 00:18:50,587
- [panicking]
- [Ame] Hurry!

414
00:18:50,671 --> 00:18:51,505
- Quick, quick!
- There!

415
00:18:51,588 --> 00:18:53,590
- [Tonet] Oh, no!
- [Ame squeals]

416
00:18:53,674 --> 00:18:54,758
[Tonet grunts]

417
00:18:54,842 --> 00:18:56,260
- [Ame] One more!
- [Karla gasps]

418
00:18:56,343 --> 00:18:58,262
- There, it's okay now.
- [Ame] It's gone.

419
00:18:58,345 --> 00:18:59,763
- [music fades]
- [Tonet sighs]

420
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:00,681
[Ame mutters]

421
00:19:00,764 --> 00:19:02,474
I'm so sorry. Are you okay?

422
00:19:02,558 --> 00:19:04,017
I'm really sorry.

423
00:19:04,101 --> 00:19:05,310
[pensive music playing]

424
00:19:05,394 --> 00:19:07,896
It's fine. You didn't mean it.

425
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:08,814
[in English] Karla, sorry.

426
00:19:08,897 --> 00:19:10,482
What you prepared got ruined.

427
00:19:11,024 --> 00:19:13,944
But wait. We can still continue the date.

428
00:19:14,027 --> 00:19:16,989
I know a nearby place.

429
00:19:17,072 --> 00:19:18,532
- [in English] Let's go. Come on.
- What about this?

430
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:20,993
I'll take care of it.

431
00:19:21,076 --> 00:19:22,202
Just continue your date.

432
00:19:22,286 --> 00:19:23,287
Are you sure?

433
00:19:23,370 --> 00:19:25,706
- No, I'll help you.
- It's fine, Gavin.

434
00:19:25,789 --> 00:19:26,623
There are plenty of them here.

435
00:19:26,707 --> 00:19:27,791
Come on. Let's go.

436
00:19:28,542 --> 00:19:29,835
[Cathy, in English] Excuse me.

437
00:19:30,502 --> 00:19:34,047
[Tonet mutters, gasps]

438
00:19:34,131 --> 00:19:38,135
If it were me,
I'd have pulled that girl's hair.

439
00:19:38,218 --> 00:19:40,804
If it were me, I'd bite her legs.

440
00:19:40,888 --> 00:19:43,140
It's obvious she did it on purpose!

441
00:19:43,223 --> 00:19:45,976
Gavin should've just courted you instead!

442
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:47,895
[Ame] Mmm-mmm.

443
00:19:47,978 --> 00:19:49,521
That won't happen.

444
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:51,857
He doesn't like me.

445
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:54,651
We're just friends, just buddies.

446
00:19:54,735 --> 00:19:56,528
Ah-- Oh, well, okay!

447
00:19:57,112 --> 00:19:58,447
Boys, let's clean this up.

448
00:19:58,530 --> 00:20:00,574
- We'll handle it. Yes.
- [Ame mutters]

449
00:20:00,657 --> 00:20:01,783
We'll take care of it.

450
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:03,327
[indistinct chattering]

451
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:04,995
[indistinct chattering]

452
00:20:05,078 --> 00:20:09,416
[music fades]

453
00:20:24,139 --> 00:20:25,140
Oh?

454
00:20:27,142 --> 00:20:28,101
Ibyang.

455
00:20:30,604 --> 00:20:32,522
Uh, what are you doing?

456
00:20:33,774 --> 00:20:35,567
[Atoy] I thought you were asleep.

457
00:20:35,651 --> 00:20:36,735
Where are you going?

458
00:20:38,195 --> 00:20:40,989
I was just looking for Sis Ame.

459
00:20:42,032 --> 00:20:43,617
She's not here. Why?

460
00:20:43,700 --> 00:20:45,285
Sis Ame isn't back yet.

461
00:20:45,369 --> 00:20:47,496
She'll be here later.
She's still at the basketball court.

462
00:20:48,413 --> 00:20:49,665
Come here, beside me.

463
00:20:53,418 --> 00:20:55,128
[melancholic music playing]

464
00:20:55,212 --> 00:20:56,505
Is there a problem?

465
00:20:57,589 --> 00:21:00,759
Did you fight with Janine again,
that's why you can't sleep?

466
00:21:02,594 --> 00:21:03,512
No.

467
00:21:04,513 --> 00:21:05,514
Uh…

468
00:21:05,597 --> 00:21:07,683
I just thought…

469
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:12,145
- Janine is rich.
- [Atoy] Hmm?

470
00:21:12,229 --> 00:21:14,648
She has her own room.

471
00:21:14,731 --> 00:21:15,732
[Atoy] Hmm?

472
00:21:15,816 --> 00:21:17,276
A big bed.

473
00:21:17,359 --> 00:21:18,402
Hmm?

474
00:21:18,485 --> 00:21:24,658
Maybe she's not used
to having someone beside her.

475
00:21:24,741 --> 00:21:27,911
So, you gave her the bed?

476
00:21:27,995 --> 00:21:29,871
You let her sleep there instead?

477
00:21:29,955 --> 00:21:31,039
Yes.

478
00:21:31,873 --> 00:21:37,212
You said we should share,
so… she can sleep there.

479
00:21:37,713 --> 00:21:40,841
And I'll just sleep beside Sis Ame.

480
00:21:42,634 --> 00:21:43,927
[in English] Wow.

481
00:21:44,011 --> 00:21:47,264
This girl is very kind.

482
00:21:47,347 --> 00:21:49,308
Hmm? Come here.

483
00:21:50,392 --> 00:21:52,728
Do you want to just stay here, beside me?

484
00:21:52,811 --> 00:21:54,604
Sis Ame will be back later anyway.

485
00:21:54,688 --> 00:21:56,064
Come on. Stay beside me, here.

486
00:21:57,691 --> 00:21:59,526
- What?
- We won't fit.

487
00:21:59,609 --> 00:22:01,737
[Atoy] Here? Says who?

488
00:22:02,863 --> 00:22:05,574
Not here, but…

489
00:22:06,325 --> 00:22:07,409
stay there.

490
00:22:07,492 --> 00:22:09,036
[light music playing]

491
00:22:16,209 --> 00:22:19,004
You know, a sofa is like fabric.

492
00:22:19,087 --> 00:22:21,381
You can twist it,

493
00:22:21,465 --> 00:22:24,384
fold it, bend it.

494
00:22:25,969 --> 00:22:26,928
Come on.

495
00:22:27,596 --> 00:22:28,472
[Atoy sighs]

496
00:22:29,973 --> 00:22:30,974
Okay?

497
00:22:32,017 --> 00:22:33,101
Is this okay?

498
00:22:33,894 --> 00:22:35,854
See, I told you.

499
00:22:35,937 --> 00:22:36,897
Wait, hold on.

500
00:22:37,397 --> 00:22:38,815
Let's turn on the aircon.

501
00:22:39,941 --> 00:22:40,942
[imitates a blipping sound]

502
00:22:41,735 --> 00:22:43,862
Ah, it's cold.

503
00:22:43,945 --> 00:22:45,864
[sighs]

504
00:22:47,324 --> 00:22:48,909
[in English] Good night, my child.

505
00:22:49,534 --> 00:22:51,119
[in English] Good night, Tatoy.

506
00:23:13,141 --> 00:23:18,563
[music intensifies]

507
00:23:18,647 --> 00:23:19,815
[door lock clicks, hinge squeaks]

508
00:23:39,251 --> 00:23:41,670
[whispers] Ibyang. Ibyang.

509
00:23:41,753 --> 00:23:43,004
[sneaky music playing]

510
00:23:43,088 --> 00:23:44,089
Ibyang.

511
00:23:46,591 --> 00:23:47,551
Ibyang.

512
00:23:47,634 --> 00:23:48,885
[sneaky music playing]

513
00:23:48,969 --> 00:23:50,303
Ibyang.

514
00:23:53,348 --> 00:23:54,641
Ouch.

515
00:23:56,726 --> 00:23:57,811
Oh?

516
00:24:00,897 --> 00:24:02,190
What are you doing--

517
00:24:02,899 --> 00:24:04,818
It's still so early. Why are you awake?

518
00:24:04,901 --> 00:24:07,154
I was looking for Ibyang.

519
00:24:08,196 --> 00:24:10,949
I thought we were sleeping side by side.

520
00:24:12,033 --> 00:24:13,368
[Atoy sighs]

521
00:24:14,786 --> 00:24:16,079
Well…

522
00:24:16,913 --> 00:24:18,748
She slept here.

523
00:24:18,832 --> 00:24:21,877
Go back to her room. Go, sleep now.

524
00:24:22,586 --> 00:24:24,379
Can you stay with me?

525
00:24:25,505 --> 00:24:29,176
I'm not used to sleeping alone here.

526
00:24:29,259 --> 00:24:30,302
Huh?

527
00:24:30,385 --> 00:24:32,554
[sneaky music playing]

528
00:24:32,637 --> 00:24:33,638
[sighs]

529
00:24:35,140 --> 00:24:36,349
Well…

530
00:24:36,933 --> 00:24:39,978
- Come on, please.
- [Atoy] Mm-hmm, okay.

531
00:25:13,595 --> 00:25:14,804
All right, come on.

532
00:25:14,888 --> 00:25:17,891
[music fades]

533
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:23,521
[music intensifies]

534
00:25:50,298 --> 00:25:52,050
- Tatoy.
- Hmm.

535
00:25:52,133 --> 00:25:54,344
Daddy, I also know how to make coffee.

536
00:25:54,427 --> 00:25:57,806
[Janine] <i>It tastes better</i>
<i>than what Ibyang made.</i>

537
00:25:57,889 --> 00:25:59,391
[retches]

538
00:25:59,474 --> 00:26:01,559
UP NEXT

539
00:26:01,643 --> 00:26:03,061
- [giggles] My phone!
- Hey!

540
00:26:03,144 --> 00:26:05,772
- Thief!
- [Emerson] You're a thief?!

541
00:26:05,855 --> 00:26:06,773
He's a thief!

542
00:26:06,856 --> 00:26:08,358
- [grunting, groaning]
- [shouting]

543
00:26:08,441 --> 00:26:09,693
[clamoring] So, you're a thief!

544
00:26:09,776 --> 00:26:11,027
[groaning, squealing]

545
00:26:11,111 --> 00:26:12,612
[Janine] <i>Why does Daddy have these?</i>

546
00:26:12,696 --> 00:26:13,655
Let's go outside.

547
00:26:13,738 --> 00:26:15,323
[Ibyang] <i>We'll both get scolded.</i>

548
00:26:15,407 --> 00:26:16,783
[dagger swishes]

549
00:26:16,866 --> 00:26:18,868
Wait. What are you doing out here?

550
00:26:18,952 --> 00:26:20,578
I already told her not to fight you.
Where is she?

551
00:26:20,662 --> 00:26:22,205
Over there in the…

552
00:26:22,289 --> 00:26:26,251
secret room, with the… clothes and knives?

553
00:26:26,334 --> 00:26:28,044
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor </i> ♪

554
00:26:28,128 --> 00:26:29,129
What?

555
00:26:29,629 --> 00:26:33,049
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

556
00:26:33,133 --> 00:26:35,302
♪ <i>Fix it</i> ♪

557
00:26:35,385 --> 00:26:36,428
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
